    "Meanwhile, a separate study of neurology inpatient encounters showed that Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) and Bidirectional and Auto-Regressive Transformers (BART) models could be used to generate summaries which met the standard of care in 62% of cases, but acknowledged that future work should count the number and type of hallucinations in automated summaries.",
    "18 Since clinicians will ultimately be responsible for auditing and modifying clinical documentation produced by LLMs, gaining a thorough understanding of potential error sources in this documentation is critically important.",
    "Without a thorough understanding of where errors may occur, there's a risk that errors made by LLMs could be overlooked, potentially harming patient care.",
